## Development Process

- ALWAYS write clean and readable code with proper comments
- Use clear, consistent naming
- Verify that each new feature works by telling the user how to test it
- Test after every meaningful change
- Think thoroughly before coding. Write 2-3 reasoning paragraphs.
- Focus on core functionality along with proper optimization

## Error Fixing

- First, explain the problem in plain English
- DO NOT JUMP TO CONCLUSIONS! Consider multiple possible causes before deciding.
- Use Sequential Thinking MCP server for critical reasoning, like solving errors

## Comments

- ALWAYS write well-documented code. Always Include LOTS of explanatory comments in code.
- Document all changes and their reasoning IN THE COMMENTS YOU WRITE
- When writing comments, use clear and easy-to-understand language. Write in short sentences.
- NEVER delete old comments - unless they are obviously wrong / obsolete
